  messages_:
  - character: {fileID: 11400000, guid: 3e0c323bd2a15d844af5a11751a9250e, type: 2}
    direction: 1
    message: 'Well done! You just triggered a cutscene. '
  - character: {fileID: 11400000, guid: 3e0c323bd2a15d844af5a11751a9250e, type: 2}
    direction: 1
    message: 'In the bottom left corner you will see grey square with some information.
      When you select a player that corresponding players health, portret and action
      points will be visible. On the bottom there is a bar that represents your health,
      when this bar is empty you have been defeated. '
  - character: {fileID: 11400000, guid: 3e0c323bd2a15d844af5a11751a9250e, type: 2}
    direction: 1
    message: When you get close enough to an enemy you will enter a combat state.
      In this state you select a player and plan out his actions ahead of time by
      rightclicking on the tiles you wish to walk. The buttons at the bottom of your
      screen will switch weapons, you can click them after you've selected your player.
  - character: {fileID: 11400000, guid: 3e0c323bd2a15d844af5a11751a9250e, type: 2}
    direction: 1
    message: To perform the actions you can either spend all your action points and
      the actions will automatically take place or press enter.
  - character: {fileID: 11400000, guid: 3e0c323bd2a15d844af5a11751a9250e, type: 2}
    direction: 1
    message: If you wish to reset your planned actions this is possible through pressing
      r. It is not possible to reset actions once they have already been performed.
  - character: {fileID: 11400000, guid: 3e0c323bd2a15d844af5a11751a9250e, type: 2}
    direction: 1
    message: Every action you do like walking, shooting and hitting with your sword
      will cost an action point. You only have a set amount of action points per
      round. When the round is over the enemy will try to defeat you.
  - character: {fileID: 11400000, guid: 3e0c323bd2a15d844af5a11751a9250e, type: 2}
    direction: 1
    message: Try walking to an enemy, selecting the player and defeat your enemy
      by equipping your rifle and shooting him! Keep your HP and Action Points in
      mind!
  - character: {fileID: 11400000, guid: 3e0c323bd2a15d844af5a11751a9250e, type: 2}
    direction: 1
    message: 'In the game there is also a initiative system. '
  - character: {fileID: 11400000, guid: 3e0c323bd2a15d844af5a11751a9250e, type: 2}
    direction: 1
    message: Combat is turn based. The system that determines what character gets
      to act in what order is called the initiative system.
  - character: {fileID: 11400000, guid: 3e0c323bd2a15d844af5a11751a9250e, type: 2}
    direction: 1
    message: The way it works is that at the start of every turn you get to plan
      the actions for all your characters.
  - character: {fileID: 11400000, guid: 3e0c323bd2a15d844af5a11751a9250e, type: 2}
    direction: 1
    message: After that is done the initiative system will determine the order based
      on how much each character wants to do.
  - character: {fileID: 11400000, guid: 3e0c323bd2a15d844af5a11751a9250e, type: 2}
    direction: 1
    message: The further you walk and the further you shoot the slower your character
      will be and the later their turn will be.
  - character: {fileID: 11400000, guid: 3e0c323bd2a15d844af5a11751a9250e, type: 2}
    direction: 1
    message: So if you want to act before your enemies think of how much your planned
      actions will cost!
